<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-15T07:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-15T07:24:00-05:00" n="773" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">311.6124/90: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-15T14:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">January 15,
                                        1921—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 3:12
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>303. Department’s number 2, January 12, 7 p.m. Complications have arisen
                            but believe I can adjust entire matter satisfactorily. Pending my
                            further telegraphic report no further deportations should be made via
                            Latvia and if any now <hi rend="italic">en route</hi> please cable me
                            immediately full information. Attitude of the Latvian authorities most
                            friendly and have no objection to further deportations but desire in the
                            meantime to effect necessary arrangements and agreement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>